<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Belarus Triple Jumper Bolts Stadium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MANNHEIM, Germany (AP) -- Natalya Kostitchenko, a Belarus triple  
jumper, ran away after winning her event in a junior track meet on 
Sunday rather than submit to doping control. 
</P>
<P>
	Kostitchenko won her event in the German Track &AMP; Field  
Federation Junior Gala in 44 feet, 6 inches, then fled after being 
informed she was one of six athletes chosen for doping control. 
</P>
<P>
	According to the Mannheimer Morgen newspaper, Kostitchenko's  
first attempt to run away ended when she was caught by stadium 
helpers at a nearby canal. 
</P>
<P>
	She was then pulled into the control room, where two Belarus  
coaches allegedly offered ``dollars or marks'' to stop the German 
doctor from testing her. 
</P>
<P>
	One of her aides then yanked the junior jumper away from the  
German officials and they ran out of the stadium. 
</P>
<P>
	Kostitchenko, who still hadn't been found by the time the  
evening banquet for athletes took place, faces a two-year 
suspension for refusing testing. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
