<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bush Uses E-Mail To Stay in Touch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- On a plane, in a car, at the office:  
Gov. Jeb Bush can often be found typing away at his laptop 
answering e-mail. 
</P>
<P>
	He's not alone. Governors around the country say they are  
turning to cyberspace to stay in touch. 
</P>
<P>
	Bush says he gets 100 e-mails a day -- from constituents,  
lawmakers, and journalists -- and responds to most of them 
personally. The personal contact is vital, he says. 
</P>
<P>
	``It is very easy to have a cocoon be built around a public  
figure,'' Bush writes in an e-mail interview with The Associated 
Press. 
</P>
<P>
	He said he spends 25 to 30 hours a week reading and responding  
to e-mail and finds it particularly helpful for staying in touch 
when he's on the road. 
</P>
<P>
	``I am on a plane flying back to Miami, drinking coffee,  
watching Shakespeare in Love (great flick) and responding to 
e-mail,'' Bush writes the next evening as the e-mail interview 
continues. 
</P>
<P>
	Across the country, most governors -- or at least their offices --  
have e-mail addresses. 
</P>
<P>
	Gov. Jesse Ventura of Minnesota gets about 120 e-mails a day,  
and staff members print out hard copy summaries for him, said 
spokeswoman Samantha Massaglia. 
</P>
<P>
	Arkansas Gov. Mike Huckabee, hooks up every day to read his  
e-mail, even when he's on holiday. 
</P>
<P>
	``If the fish aren't biting, he will check his e-mail,''  
spokesman Jim Harris said. 
</P>
<P>
	But not many governors are as reliant as Bush on e-mail to keep  
in contact with ordinary people. He may take after his father; 
former President Bush was himself a prolific letter-writer. 
</P>
<P>
	Berthy De La Rosa Aponte, a South Florida woman with a severely  
disabled daughter, says she and the governor have corresponded 
frequently about a bill to improve services for people with mental 
retardation and other developmental disabilities. 
</P>
<P>
	She said she recently sent him an e-mail, and ``he responded to  
me within the hour ... to me that's amazing.'' 
</P>
<P>
	--------	 
</P>
<P>
	Eds: Gov. Bush can be reached by e-mail directly at jeb@jeb.org  
or bushj@eog.state.fl.us 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
