<HEADLINE> Germany Wins European Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- The German men's team dominated the European Cup on  
Sunday, winning the event for the first time since 1996, while 
Russia ran away with the women's title. 
</P>
<P>
	Germany, a European Cup winner on three successive occasions  
between 1994 and 1996, ended the two-day event with 122 points. 
</P>
<P>
	Italy was second with 98 1/2, while defending champion Britain was  
third with 97. 
</P>
<P>
	Among Germany's winners Sunday were Raymond Hecht, who clinched  
the javelin with a throw of 282 feet, 3 1/2 inches, and Jurgen Schult, 
who won the discus by eight feet with a throw of 215-6. 
</P>
<P>
	One of the best races of the day saw Salvatore Vincenti of Italy  
win the 3,000 meters in 7 minutes, 59.12 seconds, just ahead of 
Russia's Vyacheslav Shabunin, 7:59.47, and Driss Maazouzi of 
France, 7:59.52. 
</P>
<P>
	The Russian women's team began the day with a nine-point lead  
over Romania, and extended it Sunday, finishing with 127 points, 28 
more than Romania. 
</P>
<P>
	Yelena Gulyayeva led the way for Russia, winning the high jump  
at 6-6 1/4. 
  	   	
</P>
