<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Nabbed for Chemical on Carousel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- A man who allegedly coated a playground  
carousel with skin-dissolving chemicals faces 12 counts of battery 
after people who were on the ride had to go to the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	Delin Swanigan, 51, was arrested and charged Saturday night,  
said Sgt. Paul Ciesielski of the Indianapolis Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
	Eleven children and one adult were sent to Methodist Hospital in  
Indianapolis with irritated skin on their faces, hands, and legs 
after riding the merry-go-round at Watkins Park on Saturday 
afternoon. They were treated and released. 
</P>
<P>
	Ciesielski said Sunday that detectives still didn't know why  
Swanigan allegedly coated the ride with a jelly-like substance. 
Officials with the state department of health still were trying to 
determine what the chemical was. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was something like a drain cleaner or some acidic type of  
solvent or paint remover,'' Ciesielski said. 
</P>
<P>
	Swanigan was being held in the Marion County Lockup and will be  
formally charged on Monday. Swanigan has refused to talk to police. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
