<HEADLINE> Braves Manager Ejected From Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- Atlanta manager Bobby Cox was thrown out of  
Sunday night's game against the Arizona Diamondbacks in the first 
inning, his fifth ejection of the season and second in five days. 
</P>
<P>
	Plate umpire Jeff Kellogg tossed Cox with one out and the bases  
loaded. 
</P>
<P>
	Cox never left the dugout before he was ejected, but he was  
letting Kellogg know what he thought of the strike zone after 
Atlanta's Tom Glavine walked two of his first four batters. 
</P>
<P>
	Kellogg walked to the dugout and warned Cox after Arizona's Matt  
Williams walked on a 3-2 pitch that loaded the bases. As Steve 
Finley prepared to bat, Kellogg turned to the dugout again, pointed 
at Cox and ordered him out of the game. 
</P>
<P>
	Cox rushed from the dugout to argue with Kellogg to the cheers  
of the big crowd. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the second time this season Cox was tossed in the first  
inning. It also happened May 11 in San Francisco. He also was 
tossed Wednesday at Houston. 
</P>
