<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Thunderstorms rippled across the northern and southern Plains on  
Sunday, and rain spread along the mid Atlantic Coast. 
</P>
<P>
	Thunderstorms and showers formed across large sections of Texas  
and spread northward into parts of Oklahoma. 
</P>
<P>
	The storms poured locally heavy rainfall on parts of Texas, with  
up to 2 inches estimated in San Patricio County, in the Corpus 
Christi area. 
</P>
<P>
	Heavy rainfall also was reported in northeastern Oklahoma.  
</P>
<P>
	The same weather system also spread widely scattered showers  
into parts of New Mexico and Colorado, with radar showing a few 
showers extending westward into sections of Arizona and Utah. 
</P>
<P>
	On the northern Plains, low pressure spread several small areas  
of strong thunderstorms and showers from eastern Montana across 
North Dakota. 
</P>
<P>
	Showers also moved across South Dakota, and thunderstorms were  
possible in western Nebraska and in parts of Minnesota and Iowa. 
</P>
<P>
	Moist air colliding with a stationary front along the East Coast  
spread clouds from Florida northward to New Jersey. 
</P>
<P>
	Within the area of clouds, showers were scattered over coastal  
sections of North Carolina and Virginia, with heavier rain 
spreading across Delaware and Maryland and moving into southern New 
Jersey. 
</P>
<P>
	Scattered storms also developed across sections of southern  
Florida. 
</P>
<P>
	Elsewhere, a few light showers were scattered over the Ohio and  
Tennessee valleys, over Upper Michigan, and across Washington and 
western Oregon. 
</P>
<P>
	Sunday's temperatures around the Lower 48 states ranged from a  
morning low of 33 at Leadville, Colo., to an early afternoon 
reading of 102 at Thermal, Calif. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
