<HEADLINE> Johnson, Knicks Each Fined $25,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Larry Johnson and the New York Knicks were each  
fined $25,000 by the NBA on Sunday because Johnson directed 
obscenities at the media earlier in the day, and failed to make 
himself available for an entire 30-minute mandatory media session. 
</P>
<P>
	This is the second series this postseason that Johnson and the  
Knicks were fined. They were also fined $10,000 by the league on 
June 8 during the Eastern Conference finals against Indiana because 
Johnson twice failed to make himself available to the media 
following practices on June 4 and 5. 
</P>
