<HEADLINE> Hynde Joining Lilith Fair Concerts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Chrissie Hynde is looking forward to joining the  
female-dominated Lilith Fair concerts this summer. But to her, the 
concept is more about star power than girl power. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's show business, isn't it?'' the leader of The Pretenders  
told the Sunday Boston Globe. 
</P>
<P>
	``Having all women is kind of a gimmick. It's entertainment. I  
don't know if it's supposed to be anything else, but for me, that's 
what it is.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hynde and The Pretenders will join a bill featuring Sarah  
McLachlan and Sheryl Crow, among others. The Pretenders' latest 
album, ``Viva L'Amore,'' is to be released Tuesday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
