<HEADLINE> Members of Internet Tax Commission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The 19 members of the Advisory Commission on Electronic  
Commerce, created by Congress to recommend in April 2000 whether 
and how Internet commerce should be taxed: 
</P>
<P>
 *Chairman    	
</P>
<P>
	--Gov. James S. Gilmore III, R-Va.  
</P>
<P>
 *Federal Officials    	
</P>
<P>
	--Andrew Pincus, Commerce Department general counsel.  
</P>
<P>
	--Joseph Guttentag, assistant Treasury secretary for  
international tax. 
</P>
<P>
	--Robert Novick, counselor to U.S. trade representative.  
</P>
<P>
 *State and Local Officials 
</P>
<P>
	--Gov. Michael O. Leavitt, R-Utah.  
</P>
<P>
	--Gov. Gary Locke, D-Wash.  
</P>
