<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Run Johnny Wins Aristides </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Run Johnny, ridden by Pat Day, closed on  
the outside and slowly pulled away for a two-length victory over 
Squall Valley in Sunday's $110,600 Grade III Aristides for 
3-year-olds and up at Churchill Downs. 
</P>
<P>
	Run Johnny, the 7-year-old gelded son of Johnny Blade, covered  
the 6 1/2 furlongs in 1:16.27 and paid $4.40, $3.20 and $2.20. 
</P>
<P>
	Squall Valley paid $8.80 and $4.60. Neon Shadow, previously  
undefeated in five career starts, finished third after setting the 
pace and paid $4.40. 
</P>
<P>
	Run Johnny, who finished third in the Churchill Downs Handicap  
on Kentucky Derby Day, earned $68,572 to increase his lifetime 
bankroll to $367,224. The victory was the 12th in 40 lifetime 
starts and second in seven this year. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
