<HEADLINE> Denver Signs Autographs on Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIDDLE BASS ISLAND, Ohio (AP) -- Gilligan isn't worried about  
getting stranded on another island. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've got my flight man waiting,'' actor Bob Denver, 64, who  
played the title role in the 1960s sitcom ``Gilligan's Island,'' 
said during an appearance Saturday on Lake Erie's Middle Bass 
Island. 
</P>
<P>
	More than 30 years after the show's prime-time run ended, fans  
still flock to see the bumbling first mate who always seemed to 
foil plans to get off the island where he and his six shipmates 
were stranded by a storm. 
</P>
<P>
	The show's 98 episodes aired on CBS from 1964-67 and can still  
be seen in syndication in more than 30 countries. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
