<HEADLINE> Gold Princess Awarded Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Gold Princess was awarded the victory in  
Sunday's $106,400 Vagrancy Handicap at Belmont Park when 
first-place Hurricane Bertie was disqualified and placed second for 
interference in the stretch. 
</P>
<P>
	Hurricane Bertie, ridden by Jorge Chavez, completed 6 1/2 furlongs  
in 1:16 2-5 and was one length ahead of Gold Princess at the 
finish. But Hurricane Bertie was penalized one spot for crossing 
over too closely in front of Gold Princess in midstretch. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold Princess, ridden by John Velazquez, won her third race in  
six starts this year and earned $63,840 for Windbound Farms. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold Princess returned $19.80, $6.10 and $4.10. Hurricane Bertie  
paid $3.40 and $2.80 and third-place Delta Music was worth $3.80. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
