<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mariners Trade Mieske for Hodges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- The Seattle Mariners cleared room for Jay  
Buhner's expected return from the disabled list by trading 
outfielder Matt Mieske to the Houston Astros on Sunday for 
right-hander Kevin Hodges. 
</P>
<P>
	Buhner, placed on the 15-day disabled list on May 19 with a  
strained left hamstring, had hoped to return for Sunday night's 
game against the Indians but had a minor setback and may not be 
back for a few more days. 
</P>
<P>
	However, in anticipation of Buhner coming back, the Mariners  
traded Mieske, who was batting .366 with four homers and seven RBIs 
in 24 games with Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
	``We were very happy with Matt Mieske's contribution to our  
ballclub,'' Seattle general manager Woody Woodward said. 
``Unfortunately, with Jay Buhner expected to return from the 
disabled list soon, we had to make this move to clear a spot on our 
roster.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hodges began the season with Double-A Jackson of the Texas  
League where he went 1-4 with a 2.94 ERA in eight starts before 
being promoted to Triple-A New Orleans. He was 1-3 at New Orleans 
with a 7.24 ERA in five starts. 
</P>
<P>
	The Mariners said Hodges will probably report to Triple-A  
Tacoma. 
</P>
<P>
	Buhner was batting .268 with six homers and 18 RBIs in 26 games  
before he was injured in a May 18 game against Minnesota. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
